Defendant Daleon D Jackson in court with attorney Dianne Margaret Erickson.  Defendant Daleon D Jackson in custody.  Michael Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Court finds the State has complied with the victim rights legislation. PSI reviewed by the parties. Statements made as to sentencing.

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 7 YEARS, with credit for 129 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 5 YEARS.  

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
1) Court set restitution at ZERO;
2) No contact with the victim;
3) No contact with non-biological children under the age of 16 years without permission of the agent;
4) Participate in educational programming or vocational programming or a combination of both;
5) Defendant is prohibited from particpating in social media. Defendant may have an email account;
6) Any electronic devices must be turned over to agent for inspection upon demand;
7) Maintain absolute sobriety from all illegal substances;
8) Register/comply with the sex offender registry;
9) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
10) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;

Court recommends the defendant participate in the Denier's Group treatment and therapy as mentioned in the Presentence Investigation Report. 

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. 

Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 

Court advised defendant if he is not a citizen of the United States of America, that upon a plea of guilty or no contest for this offense, he could be deported, excluded from admission to his country, or denied naturalization under federal law.  

Court advised that the defendant will have to provide a DNA sample, to the Wisconsin State Crime Laboratory for DNA testing and pay a DNA surcharge.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
